---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Context Continuity Protocol (CCP) — LeanCTX"
  description="CCP gives your AI memory that persists across chat sessions. Restore previous session state in ~400 tokens instead of re-reading 50,000 tokens of context."
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
    { name: 'Protocols', url: '/protocols' },
    { name: 'CCP', url: '/protocols/ccp' },
  ]}
>


<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     HERO
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section-y">
  <div class="content-grid">
    <div class="animate-entrance">
      <p class="fluid-label text-muted" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 1vw, 2.5rem);">
        Protocols / CCP
      </p>
    </div>

    <h1 class="font-display fluid-h1 font-bold text-text-bright animate-entrance stagger-1" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1.5rem, 1rem + 1.5vw, 3rem);">
      Context Continuity Protocol.
    </h1>

    <p class="fluid-body text-muted animate-entrance stagger-2" style="margin-bottom: clamp(2.5rem, 2rem + 2vw, 5rem); max-width: 44rem;">
      CCP gives your AI memory that persists across chat sessions and context compactions.
      Instead of re-reading 50,000 tokens of context on every new conversation,
      CCP restores the previous session state in approximately 400 tokens.
    </p>

    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center animate-entrance stagger-3" style="gap: clamp(0.75rem, 0.5rem + 0.5vw, 1.25rem);">
      <a href="/docs/getting-started" class="btn-primary inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg" style="padding: clamp(0.7rem, 0.55rem + 0.3vw, 0.9rem) clamp(1.5rem, 1rem + 0.75vw, 2.25rem); font-size: clamp(0.8125rem, 0.78rem + 0.15vw, 0.9375rem);">
        Get Started
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"/></svg>
      </a>
      <a href="/protocols" class="btn-outline inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg" style="padding: clamp(0.7rem, 0.55rem + 0.3vw, 0.9rem) clamp(1.5rem, 1rem + 0.75vw, 2.25rem); font-size: clamp(0.8125rem, 0.78rem + 0.15vw, 0.9375rem);">
        All Protocols
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<div class="section-divider content-grid"></div>


<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     THE COLD START PROBLEM
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section-y">
  <div class="content-grid">
    <p class="fluid-label text-muted animate-entrance" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.5vw, 1.5rem);">
      The Problem
    </p>
    <h2 class="font-display fluid-h2 font-bold text-text-bright animate-entrance stagger-1" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.5vw, 2rem);">
      The Cold Start Problem.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-muted fluid-body animate-entrance stagger-2" style="margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 2rem + 3vw, 6rem); max-width: 44rem;">
      Every new chat session starts with zero context. The AI knows nothing about your project,
      your architecture, your recent changes, or what you were working on five minutes ago.
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 animate-entrance stagger-3" style="gap: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.75vw, 1.5rem);">
      <div class="ccp-problem-card">
        <div class="ccp-problem-header ccp-problem-header--bad">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M18.364 18.364A9 9 0 005.636 5.636m12.728 12.728A9 9 0 015.636 5.636m12.728 12.728L5.636 5.636"/></svg>
          Traditional approach
        </div>
        <div class="ccp-problem-body font-mono" style="font-size: clamp(0.6875rem, 0.65rem + 0.1vw, 0.8125rem);">
          <div class="ccp-problem-line"><span class="text-muted">New chat session starts</span></div>
          <div class="ccp-problem-line"><span class="text-danger">AI has zero project context</span></div>
          <div class="ccp-problem-line"><span class="text-muted">Re-read all files, re-discover architecture</span></div>
          <div class="ccp-problem-line"><span class="text-danger">~50,000 tokens wasted every time</span></div>
          <div class="ccp-problem-line"><span class="text-muted">Slow start, repeated questions, lost decisions</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ccp-problem-card">
        <div class="ccp-problem-header ccp-problem-header--good">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/></svg>
          With CCP
        </div>
        <div class="ccp-problem-body font-mono" style="font-size: clamp(0.6875rem, 0.65rem + 0.1vw, 0.8125rem);">
          <div class="ccp-problem-line"><span class="text-muted">New chat session starts</span></div>
          <div class="ccp-problem-line"><span class="text-accent">ctx_session load restores previous state</span></div>
          <div class="ccp-problem-line"><span class="text-muted">Task, findings, decisions, file refs — all intact</span></div>
          <div class="ccp-problem-line"><span class="text-accent">~400 tokens — picks up exactly where it left off</span></div>
          <div class="ccp-problem-line"><span class="text-muted">Immediate productivity, no warm-up needed</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<div class="section-divider content-grid"></div>


<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     SESSION COMMANDS
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section-y">
  <div class="content-grid">
    <p class="fluid-label text-muted animate-entrance" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.5vw, 1.5rem);">
      Commands
    </p>
    <h2 class="font-display fluid-h2 font-bold text-text-bright animate-entrance stagger-1" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.5vw, 2rem);">
      Session Commands.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-muted fluid-body animate-entrance stagger-2" style="margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 2rem + 3vw, 6rem); max-width: 44rem;">
      CCP exposes a set of session management commands through the MCP server.
      The AI calls these automatically based on context — you can also invoke them manually.
    </p>

    <div class="ccp-table-wrapper animate-entrance stagger-3">
      <table class="ccp-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th class="text-text-bright">Command</th>
            <th class="text-text-bright">Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code class="ccp-code">ctx_session status</code></td>
            <td class="text-muted">Show current session state — version, call count, active task, cached files</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code class="ccp-code">ctx_session load</code></td>
            <td class="text-muted">Restore previous session from disk — cross-chat memory in ~400 tokens</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code class="ccp-code">ctx_session task "description"</code></td>
            <td class="text-muted">Set the current task — persisted across sessions for continuity</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code class="ccp-code">ctx_session finding "file:line — summary"</code></td>
            <td class="text-muted">Record a key finding — bugs, patterns, important code locations</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code class="ccp-code">ctx_session decision "summary"</code></td>
            <td class="text-muted">Record an architectural decision — prevents re-debating resolved choices</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code class="ccp-code">ctx_session save</code></td>
            <td class="text-muted">Force persist session state to disk — normally auto-saved</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code class="ccp-code">ctx_wrapped [period]</code></td>
            <td class="text-muted">Generate a savings report card — token savings, cache hit rates, compression stats</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<div class="section-divider content-grid"></div>


<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     LITM-AWARE POSITIONING
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section-y">
  <div class="content-grid">
    <p class="fluid-label text-muted animate-entrance" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.5vw, 1.5rem);">
      Research-Backed
    </p>
    <h2 class="font-display fluid-h2 font-bold text-text-bright animate-entrance stagger-1" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.5vw, 2rem);">
      LITM-Aware Positioning.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-muted fluid-body animate-entrance stagger-2" style="margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 2rem + 3vw, 6rem); max-width: 44rem;">
      LLMs do not attend equally to all tokens. Research by Liu et al. (2023) showed that
      models pay significantly more attention to tokens at the beginning and end of the context window,
      while middle tokens get "lost" with lower attention weights. CCP exploits this directly.
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 animate-entrance stagger-3" style="gap: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.75vw, 1.5rem); margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 2rem + 3vw, 5rem);">
      <div class="card ccp-position-card">
        <div class="ccp-position-label" style="color: var(--color-accent);">Begin Position</div>
        <div class="ccp-position-alpha font-display font-bold" style="color: var(--color-accent);">alpha = 0.9</div>
        <p class="fluid-sm text-muted" style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">
          Highest attention weight. CCP places task description, architectural decisions,
          project topology, and file reference map here.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card ccp-position-card">
        <div class="ccp-position-label" style="color: var(--color-accent-3);">Middle Position</div>
        <div class="ccp-position-alpha font-display font-bold" style="color: var(--color-accent-3);">beta = 0.55</div>
        <p class="fluid-sm text-muted" style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">
          Lowest attention weight — the "lost in the middle" zone. Historical context
          and lower-priority information goes here.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card ccp-position-card">
        <div class="ccp-position-label" style="color: var(--color-accent-2);">End Position</div>
        <div class="ccp-position-alpha font-display font-bold" style="color: var(--color-accent-2);">gamma = 0.85</div>
        <p class="fluid-sm text-muted" style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">
          Second-highest attention. CCP places recent findings, test results,
          and next steps here for immediate relevance.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="animate-entrance stagger-4">
      <p class="fluid-label text-muted" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.5vw, 1.5rem);">
        Model-Specific Profiles
      </p>
      <div class="ccp-table-wrapper">
        <table class="ccp-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th class="text-text-bright">Model</th>
              <th class="text-text-bright">Alpha (begin)</th>
              <th class="text-text-bright">Beta (middle)</th>
              <th class="text-text-bright">Gamma (end)</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="text-text-bright font-medium">Claude</td>
              <td><span class="text-accent font-mono">0.92</span></td>
              <td><span class="text-accent-3 font-mono">0.50</span></td>
              <td><span class="text-accent-2 font-mono">0.88</span></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="text-text-bright font-medium">GPT</td>
              <td><span class="text-accent font-mono">0.90</span></td>
              <td><span class="text-accent-3 font-mono">0.55</span></td>
              <td><span class="text-accent-2 font-mono">0.85</span></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="text-text-bright font-medium">Gemini</td>
              <td><span class="text-accent font-mono">0.88</span></td>
              <td><span class="text-accent-3 font-mono">0.60</span></td>
              <td><span class="text-accent-2 font-mono">0.82</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<div class="section-divider content-grid"></div>


<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     AUTO-CHECKPOINT SYSTEM
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section-y">
  <div class="content-grid">
    <p class="fluid-label text-muted animate-entrance" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.5vw, 1.5rem);">
      Automatic
    </p>
    <h2 class="font-display fluid-h2 font-bold text-text-bright animate-entrance stagger-1" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.5vw, 2rem);">
      Auto-Checkpoint System.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-muted fluid-body animate-entrance stagger-2" style="margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 2rem + 3vw, 6rem); max-width: 44rem;">
      Long sessions accumulate context. Without intervention, the context window fills up
      and the AI loses track of earlier work. CCP prevents this automatically.
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 animate-entrance stagger-3" style="gap: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.75vw, 1.5rem);">
      <div class="card ccp-feature-card">
        <h3 class="fluid-h3 font-display font-semibold text-text-bright" style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
          Every 15 tool calls
        </h3>
        <p class="fluid-sm text-muted">
          lean-ctx automatically creates a compressed checkpoint combined with the current session state.
          The checkpoint captures task, findings, decisions, and file references in a compact format.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card ccp-feature-card">
        <h3 class="fluid-h3 font-display font-semibold text-text-bright" style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
          Configurable interval
        </h3>
        <p class="fluid-sm text-muted">
          Set <code class="ccp-code">LEAN_CTX_CHECKPOINT_INTERVAL</code> to adjust the checkpoint frequency.
          Lower values create more frequent checkpoints for very long sessions.
          Higher values reduce overhead for shorter workflows.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card ccp-feature-card">
        <h3 class="fluid-h3 font-display font-semibold text-text-bright" style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
          Keeps context compact
        </h3>
        <p class="fluid-sm text-muted">
          Each checkpoint compresses the accumulated context, preventing the window from bloating.
          The AI retains all critical information while discarding redundant intermediate states.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card ccp-feature-card">
        <h3 class="fluid-h3 font-display font-semibold text-text-bright" style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
          Zero user intervention
        </h3>
        <p class="fluid-sm text-muted">
          Checkpoints happen transparently. The AI doesn't pause, doesn't ask permission,
          and doesn't interrupt your workflow. The compressed state is appended to the response automatically.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<div class="section-divider content-grid"></div>


<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     IDLE CACHE TTL
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section-y">
  <div class="content-grid">
    <p class="fluid-label text-muted animate-entrance" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.5vw, 1.5rem);">
      Cache Management
    </p>
    <h2 class="font-display fluid-h2 font-bold text-text-bright animate-entrance stagger-1" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.5vw, 2rem);">
      Idle Cache TTL.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-muted fluid-body animate-entrance stagger-2" style="margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 2rem + 3vw, 6rem); max-width: 44rem;">
      Stale cached data from a previous session can pollute a new conversation.
      CCP automatically clears the cache after inactivity, ensuring every new session starts clean.
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 animate-entrance stagger-3" style="gap: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.75vw, 1.5rem);">
      <div class="card ccp-feature-card">
        <h3 class="fluid-h3 font-display font-semibold text-text-bright" style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
          5-minute TTL
        </h3>
        <p class="fluid-sm text-muted">
          After 5 minutes of inactivity — triggered by a new chat or context compaction —
          the file cache auto-clears. This prevents outdated file contents from leaking into new sessions.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card ccp-feature-card">
        <h3 class="fluid-h3 font-display font-semibold text-text-bright" style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
          Session state preserved
        </h3>
        <p class="fluid-sm text-muted">
          Before clearing the cache, CCP auto-saves the session state to disk.
          The task, findings, decisions, and file reference map survive the cache clear
          and can be restored with <code class="ccp-code">ctx_session load</code>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card ccp-feature-card">
        <h3 class="fluid-h3 font-display font-semibold text-text-bright" style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
          Configurable
        </h3>
        <p class="fluid-sm text-muted">
          Set <code class="ccp-code">LEAN_CTX_CACHE_TTL</code> in seconds to adjust the idle timeout.
          Set to <code class="ccp-code">0</code> to disable automatic cache clearing entirely.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card ccp-feature-card">
        <h3 class="fluid-h3 font-display font-semibold text-text-bright" style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
          Clean session boundary
        </h3>
        <p class="fluid-sm text-muted">
          When you start a new chat, the AI gets fresh file reads instead of stale cached versions.
          Combined with session restore, this gives the best of both worlds — continuity without staleness.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<div class="section-divider content-grid"></div>


<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     SUBAGENT ISOLATION
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section-y">
  <div class="content-grid">
    <p class="fluid-label text-muted animate-entrance" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.5vw, 1.5rem);">
      Isolation
    </p>
    <h2 class="font-display fluid-h2 font-bold text-text-bright animate-entrance stagger-1" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.5vw, 2rem);">
      Subagent Isolation.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-muted fluid-body animate-entrance stagger-2" style="margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 2rem + 3vw, 6rem); max-width: 44rem;">
      Modern AI tools spawn subagents — independent workers that run in parallel.
      Each subagent needs its own fresh context, not the parent agent's cached state.
      CCP provides mechanisms to prevent cache leakage.
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 animate-entrance stagger-3" style="gap: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.75vw, 1.5rem);">
      <div class="card ccp-feature-card">
        <div class="ccp-code-badge font-mono" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">fresh=true</div>
        <p class="fluid-sm text-muted">
          Pass <code class="ccp-code">fresh=true</code> to any <code class="ccp-code">ctx_read</code> call
          to bypass the cache entirely. The file is read from disk and the result is not cached.
          Use when spawned as a subagent or after context compaction.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card ccp-feature-card">
        <div class="ccp-code-badge font-mono" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">ctx_cache clear</div>
        <p class="fluid-sm text-muted">
          Resets the entire file cache. Use when switching between unrelated tasks
          or when the cached state has diverged from disk.
          Session state is preserved — only file content cache is cleared.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card ccp-feature-card">
        <div class="ccp-code-badge font-mono" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">ctx_cache invalidate</div>
        <p class="fluid-sm text-muted">
          Invalidate a single file's cache entry by path.
          Use after external edits (e.g., another tool modified the file)
          to ensure the next read reflects the current disk state.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<div class="section-divider content-grid"></div>


<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     TERMINAL DEMO
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section-y">
  <div class="content-grid">
    <p class="fluid-label text-muted animate-entrance" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.5vw, 1.5rem);">
      In Action
    </p>
    <h2 class="font-display fluid-h2 font-bold text-text-bright animate-entrance stagger-1" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.5vw, 2rem);">
      Session restore in your terminal.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-muted fluid-body animate-entrance stagger-2" style="margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 2rem + 3vw, 5rem); max-width: 44rem;">
      This is what happens when you start a new chat. The AI calls <code class="ccp-code">ctx_session load</code>
      and instantly has full project context — task, findings, decisions, and file references.
    </p>

    <div class="terminal-chrome animate-entrance stagger-3" style="max-width: 48rem;">
      <div class="terminal-header flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2.5">
        <span class="terminal-dot bg-[#ff5f57]"></span>
        <span class="terminal-dot bg-[#febc2e]"></span>
        <span class="terminal-dot bg-[#28c840]"></span>
        <span class="ml-3 text-xs text-muted font-mono">ctx_session load</span>
      </div>
      <div class="terminal-body px-5 py-5 font-mono space-y-3" style="font-size: clamp(0.6875rem, 0.65rem + 0.1vw, 0.8125rem); line-height: 1.7;">
        <div>
          <span class="text-accent-2 font-bold">SESSION RESTORED</span> <span class="text-muted">v191 | 761 calls | 282,179 tok saved</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ccp-term-divider"></div>
        <div>
          <span class="text-muted">Task:</span> <span class="text-text-bright">Auth refactor — JWT to session tokens</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ccp-term-divider"></div>
        <div>
          <span class="text-muted">Decisions:</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pl-4">
          <span class="text-text">Use Redis for session storage</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pl-4">
          <span class="text-text">Keep JWT for API-only routes</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pl-4">
          <span class="text-text">Migrate incrementally, not big-bang</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ccp-term-divider"></div>
        <div>
          <span class="text-muted">Findings:</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pl-4">
          <span class="text-text-bright">auth.ts:42</span> <span class="text-muted">— expiry check uses wrong clock source</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pl-4">
          <span class="text-text-bright">session.ts:18</span> <span class="text-muted">— missing refresh token rotation</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pl-4">
          <span class="text-text-bright">middleware.ts:7</span> <span class="text-muted">— no rate limiting on token endpoint</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ccp-term-divider"></div>
        <div>
          <span class="text-muted">Files (8):</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pl-4">
          <span class="text-accent">[F1 auth.ts full]</span>
          <span class="text-accent">[F2 session.ts full]</span>
